1
00:00:00,940 --> 00:00:07,940

2
00:00:09,780 --> 00:00:13,640

3
00:00:13,640 --> 00:00:17,210

4
00:00:17,210 --> 00:00:20,780

5
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:25,220

6
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:29,330

7
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:33,500

8
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:38,220

9
00:00:42,150 --> 00:00:45,440

10
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:50,030

11
00:00:51,450 --> 00:00:53,390
Sir,

12
00:00:55,340 --> 00:00:57,660
do you like me?

13
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:01,470
What?

14
00:01:01,471 --> 00:01:05,789
Telling me that I'll meet someone that's a million times better...

15
00:01:05,790 --> 00:01:08,310
Do you mean yourself?

16
00:01:08,310 --> 00:01:09,490
♫  When I’m in your atmosphere  ♫

17
00:01:09,490 --> 00:01:13,040
You like me, don't you?

18
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,629
I'm right.

19
00:01:14,630 --> 00:01:16,319
Aren't I?

20
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:20,279
Can I... give you an answer this way?

21
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:21,910
Sir?

22
00:01:21,910 --> 00:01:25,120
♫  Just listen here we are again  ♫

23
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,670
♫  Through the fire through the rain  ♫

24
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:30,020
♫  The roads we crossed they built  ♫

25
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:32,230
♫  Story of us  ♫

26
00:01:32,230 --> 00:01:34,220
Why did I ask?

27
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,440
 Editor Na Zero Won.

28
00:01:39,230 --> 00:01:40,919
 Look here, Editor Na Zero Won.

29
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:42,620
 Pardon?

30
00:01:43,781 --> 00:01:46,120
 What did you just say?

31
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:48,490
 I said...

32
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,750
 I mean...

33
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:57,340
 Do you like me?

34
00:01:57,340 --> 00:01:59,139
 Can I give you an answer this way?

35
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:00,700
 Sir?

36
00:02:04,310 --> 00:02:06,919
 Get a grip.

37
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:10,700
 I told you to drink freely, not get drunk freely.

38
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:16,410
 Come on. I'm right, right?

39
00:02:16,410 --> 00:02:18,579
 I already know!

40
00:02:18,580 --> 00:02:21,150
 You paid for the armchair and coffee.

41
00:02:21,150 --> 00:02:24,219
 You stopped me from buying drinks.

42
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:26,880
 You're buying me drinks now.

43
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:32,209
 You say it's about legal matters or efficiency,

44
00:02:32,209 --> 00:02:34,969
 but it's all an excuse.

45
00:02:34,970 --> 00:02:36,839
 Since you like me,

46
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:41,290
 you want to treat me well, so you made excuses!

47
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:52,599
 Since it's all out in the open, just be honest and tell me.

48
00:02:52,599 --> 00:02:56,680
 Like a man! Be brave!

49
00:03:01,110 --> 00:03:04,390
 Can I really be honest?

50
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:09,129
 I did it because I took pity on you.

51
00:03:09,129 --> 00:03:11,720
 Because you're pitiful.

52
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,139
 Pardon?

53
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:15,320
 Trembling at spending ₩10,000 ($10) while trying to save up for a house at your age,

54
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:18,089
 I felt pity for you, that's why.

55
00:03:18,090 --> 00:03:20,289
 I was helping like I would the needy.

56
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:22,330
 Happy now?

57
00:03:22,330 --> 00:03:25,000
 The needy?

58
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,699
 Wow, I can't believe you'd misunderstand something like that!

59
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:28,429
 I'm Gaeryong Yoo Ja Sung.

60
00:03:28,430 --> 00:03:30,809
 The last dragon of our age to rise from a ditch.

61
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:34,289
 Do you think I became a dragon to be with someone like you?

62
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:37,149
 Do you think I became self-made just to be with someone like you?

63
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:39,420
 Get a grip! Please!

64
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:42,320
 What do I do now?

65
00:03:43,530 --> 00:03:46,609
I should die.

66
00:03:46,610 --> 00:03:48,470
Die.

67
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:54,410
I can't go to work tomorrow.

68
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:59,119
  I shouldn't have been nice to her, no matter how pitiful she is.

69
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,769
 Me, like Na Zero Won?

70
00:04:00,770 --> 00:04:02,159
 Me, Gaeryong Yoo Ja Sung?

71
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:04,069
 Na Zero Won who has nothing?

72
00:04:04,070 --> 00:04:05,279
I'll turn up the volume.

73
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:07,840
What a load of rubbish!

74
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:10,240
I'm sorry.

75
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,909
Oh, no.

76
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:14,710
I wasn't talking to you.

77
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:18,069
Why does my car have a taximeter?

78
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:19,060
What?

79
00:04:19,061 --> 00:04:20,679
It's my car. A taxi.

80
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,139
Taxi?

81
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:23,319
Aren't you the chauffeur?

82
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,270
I'm a taxi driver.

83
00:04:24,271 --> 00:04:25,629
- Then what about my car? 
 - Pardon?

84
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:27,360
Pardon?

85
00:04:28,710 --> 00:04:30,950
Oh, no.

86
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:35,419
I think I called a taxi instead of the chauffeur service.

87
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:38,279
I'm sorry, but please turn back to Itaewon.

88
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:40,090
Sure.

89
00:04:41,170 --> 00:04:44,109
 I can't believe I made a mistake like this. I'm always perfect.

90
00:04:44,110 --> 00:04:47,810
  But then again, she did cause huge mental damage.

91
00:04:47,810 --> 00:04:50,889
 I'm wasting money, time, and emotions.

92
00:04:50,890 --> 00:04:52,750
 This is all because of Na Zero Won.

93
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:55,289
 Na Zero Won. Na Zero Won.

94
00:04:55,290 --> 00:04:57,830
Na Zero Won!

95
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:16,300
Hello, sir!

96
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:18,610
What a lovely morning!

97
00:05:18,610 --> 00:05:20,219
Lovely morning? Yesterday, don't you—

98
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:23,990
Oh. Did you get home safe?

99
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:27,790
I blacked out. I don't remember a thing.

100
00:05:27,790 --> 00:05:29,829
Oh, I see.

101
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:31,809
You did look very drunk.

102
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:34,290
Tell me about it!

103
00:05:34,290 --> 00:05:37,789
I should end my drinking or my life.

104
00:05:37,790 --> 00:05:40,319
Right. I told you I was buying you a drink,

105
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,409
but the bill was more than I expected.

106
00:05:42,410 --> 00:05:45,440
I was thinking we should split it.

107
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,490
How much was it?

108
00:05:46,490 --> 00:05:49,680
- ₩380,000 ($380). 
 - Pardon?

109
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:53,429
But we had two glasses of draft beer and six bottled beers.

110
00:05:53,429 --> 00:05:54,909
As a snack, we had shrimp gambas.

111
00:05:54,910 --> 00:05:57,690
The total is probably less than ₩100,000 ($100).

112
00:05:57,690 --> 00:06:00,039
That chicken salad was on the house.

113
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:03,360
You seem to remember perfectly well.

114
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,189
It's not that you don't remember.

115
00:06:06,189 --> 00:06:10,280
It's that you don't want to remember what you did yesterday.

116
00:06:10,970 --> 00:06:14,540
I felt so embarrassed.

117
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:16,830
I'm sorry.

118
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:20,059
I'm sorry about yesterday too.

119
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:22,160
You're sorry...

120
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:25,009
You were out of line, and then you lied again. Do you think sorry will suffice?

121
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:27,759
That doesn't make what you did go away.

122
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:29,530
Sir?

123
00:06:29,530 --> 00:06:32,049
The feeling of insult you left me with...

124
00:06:32,050 --> 00:06:34,879
That won't go away with the word "sorry."

125
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:36,980
Got it?

126
00:06:44,450 --> 00:06:47,150
What am I going to do?

127
00:06:49,430 --> 00:06:51,240
Great.

128
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:54,859
Hello.

129
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:56,069
- Hi. 
 - Hello.

130
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:58,159
What? Did your interview end late?

131
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,230
You look so tired.

132
00:07:00,230 --> 00:07:01,299
You know how it's like.

133
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:03,510
Yes, I know.

134
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:08,459
I'm also very tired.

135
00:07:08,460 --> 00:07:13,299
So... How about a cup of sweet coffee to recharge our energy?

136
00:07:13,299 --> 00:07:14,549
Are you buying?

137
00:07:14,550 --> 00:07:16,750
Are you crazy?

138
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:20,449
The person who was supposed to buy us drinks at the popular pork ribs place,

139
00:07:20,450 --> 00:07:23,639
but who luckily got away without buying.

140
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:25,919
Who is that damn lucky woman?

141
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:30,340
Her name is Na. Young. Won.

142
00:07:30,340 --> 00:07:32,549
Editor Na should buy.

143
00:07:32,550 --> 00:07:33,649
But!

144
00:07:33,650 --> 00:07:35,190
No.

145
00:07:35,190 --> 00:07:40,820
We have another financier.

146
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:44,320
Pardon?

147
00:07:44,321 --> 00:07:49,280
Well, actually, I was going to ask Editor Na to buy coffee since she got out of it thanks to you.

148
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:51,370
That was my plan, but right then,

149
00:07:51,370 --> 00:07:56,010
your wise remarks suddenly brushed past my thoughts.

150
00:07:56,010 --> 00:07:57,929
- Wise remarks? 
 - Yes.

151
00:07:57,930 --> 00:07:59,939
The wise remark where you said

152
00:07:59,940 --> 00:08:03,899
it's only right that you buy the coffee to boost work efficiency.

153
00:08:03,899 --> 00:08:07,749
So I've come to ask politely.

154
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,650
I did well, right?

155
00:08:09,650 --> 00:08:11,379
What about my work efficiency?

156
00:08:11,380 --> 00:08:12,370
Sir?

157
00:08:12,371 --> 00:08:15,779
If I buy coffee, your team will perform well.

158
00:08:15,779 --> 00:08:17,740
However, what about me?

159
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:20,439
I have the most important position in this publishing company.

160
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:23,800
My work efficiency will decrease.

161
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:26,639
What happened? What happened?

162
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:30,110
He said Editor Na should just buy coffee.

163
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:31,259
Wait, but last time...

164
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:32,909
Right. Last time, I bought coffee.

165
00:08:32,910 --> 00:08:35,139
I'm deeply regretting that moment.

166
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:38,340
I shouldn't have wasted my money like that.

167
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:43,249
What's the most expensive coffee on the menu?

168
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:46,830
Green tea cream latte blended.

169
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:48,069
Anything more expensive?

170
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:50,090
You can upgrade the size to a large one.

171
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:51,320
And add Java chip sprinkles on top.

172
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,519
And add hazelnut syrup.

173
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,470
And get a drizzle topping.

174
00:08:53,471 --> 00:08:55,309
And two or three shots of espresso—

175
00:08:55,310 --> 00:08:56,699
Stop!

176
00:08:56,700 --> 00:09:00,850
Add in everything that's available!

177
00:09:02,380 --> 00:09:03,699
What's up with him?

178
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:06,419
He must really regret buying coffee last time.

179
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:09,829
Anyway, I'll have what he's having.

180
00:09:09,830 --> 00:09:11,809
- Me, too. 
 - Come on.

181
00:09:11,810 --> 00:09:14,299
Young Won doesn't have any money.

182
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:15,799
I'll buy.

183
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,009
It's okay, Sunbae.

184
00:09:17,010 --> 00:09:18,809
- I'll buy. 
 - Forget it.

185
00:09:18,810 --> 00:09:22,430
I told you I would help you save up.

186
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:25,890

187
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,370
 Thanks, Sunbae.

188
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,989
I'm getting a hunch.

189
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:35,749
What? About what?

190
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:39,119
I thought I lost my touch last time.

191
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:43,400
But now I'm sure that CEO Yoo likes you.

192
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,089
Not this again, please.

193
00:09:46,090 --> 00:09:47,259
What do you mean?

194
00:09:47,260 --> 00:09:49,099
Last time, he bought coffee in your place stead.

195
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:50,929
Today, he tells you to buy coffee.

196
00:09:50,930 --> 00:09:52,300
What do you think he's doing?

197
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,859
He's playing tug-of-war.

198
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:56,360
No, he's not.

199
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,229
What do you think of him?

200
00:09:58,230 --> 00:09:59,650
He's surly,

201
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:02,769
but he's not so terrible to flirt with.

202
00:10:02,770 --> 00:10:06,039
Stop it! I told you he doesn't like me.

203
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,649
I'm telling you he does!

204
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:09,779
If you don't believe me, ask him yourself.

205
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:12,969
Ask him directly if he likes you.

206
00:10:12,970 --> 00:10:15,129
- Ask him right— 
 - I did.

207
00:10:15,130 --> 00:10:16,819
I asked him!

208
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:18,330
What?

209
00:10:20,590 --> 00:10:22,720
I'm going crazy.

210
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:26,050

211
00:10:26,050 --> 00:10:28,949
The client of last quarter's interior special "Change"

212
00:10:28,950 --> 00:10:33,040
was a newly-wed couple in their thirties, living in a monthly rented house.

213
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:35,280
The client chosen for this quarter

214
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:38,519
is a single mom renting a single-room apartment.

215
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,510
Stop.

216
00:10:39,511 --> 00:10:40,799
Change the client.

217
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:41,640
Sir?

218
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:44,539
Who would be interested in a single-room interior?

219
00:10:44,540 --> 00:10:47,399
Changing a single room won't draw attention.

220
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:49,950
Change it to the vacation home I invested in.

221
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:52,269
Sir, but that's...

222
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:56,049
This special is to help out the marginalized...

223
00:10:56,050 --> 00:10:59,740
I need to change someone else along with the client.

224
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:01,259
Do you mean me again?

225
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:02,210
Yes.

226
00:11:02,211 --> 00:11:05,069
I can't work with someone who disagrees with me.

227
00:11:05,070 --> 00:11:08,329
I'll calmly change the client.

228
00:11:08,330 --> 00:11:11,709
I didn't buy this magazine to do charity work.

229
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:14,269
But if you help, you'll feel rewarded—

230
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:15,559
Rewarded?

231
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:17,129
I don't know about that.

232
00:11:17,130 --> 00:11:19,809
There was an instance where I helped out a disadvantaged person

233
00:11:19,810 --> 00:11:24,110
and instead of feeling rewarded, I was ridiculously misunderstood.

234
00:11:34,730 --> 00:11:38,900
He was ridiculously misunderstood after helping out a disadvantaged person...

235
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:41,100
He was saying that to you, right?

236
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:44,100
Now that I think about it, saying that he deeply regrets buying coffee

237
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:46,200
was for you to hear as well.

238
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:49,390
He's raking you over methodically.

239
00:11:49,390 --> 00:11:51,049
What do I do now?

240
00:11:51,050 --> 00:11:52,809
So why did you ask him?

241
00:11:52,810 --> 00:11:56,540
Why get raked over by asking him if he likes you so rashly?

242
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:59,149
You said your hunch was right.

243
00:11:59,150 --> 00:12:03,120
You said you were sure he liked me.

244
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:05,089
- You seem so foreign to me. 
 - Pardon?

245
00:12:05,090 --> 00:12:09,160
When have you ever listened to me so well?

246
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:10,889
What are you going to do now?

247
00:12:10,890 --> 00:12:14,360
I'm so worried about you!

248
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:27,760
I heard someone moved into #707.

249
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:30,099
Do they know what happened there?

250
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:31,789
If she did, she wouldn't have moved in.

251
00:12:31,790 --> 00:12:34,150
She lives alone, on top of that.

252
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:37,099
What... are you talking about?

253
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:39,580
We'll be going now.

254
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:42,740
What happened in #707?

255
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:44,440
Nothing. It's nothing.

256
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:47,570
What do you mean, "nothing"? What happened?

257
00:12:47,570 --> 00:12:49,969
 I think it was about a year ago.

258
00:12:49,970 --> 00:12:54,369
 A woman about your age lived in #707.

259
00:12:54,370 --> 00:12:56,810
 She committed suicide.

260
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:04,819
 Word got around, and no one wanted to live there.

261
00:13:04,819 --> 00:13:06,579
 Some moved in without knowing,

262
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:08,819
 but they didn't last a month.

263
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:13,600
 They said there was a ghost.

264
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:18,380
Come on. There's no ghost.

265
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:21,690
It's the Forth Industrial Revolution era.

266
00:13:21,690 --> 00:13:25,100
AIs park cars nowadays.

267
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:27,360
Ghosts aren't real.

268
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,269
 No need to thank me.

269
00:13:41,270 --> 00:13:44,309
  I'm getting monthly rent from a spare apartment.

270
00:13:44,310 --> 00:13:47,090
 A spare apartment?

271
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:54,509
He should have told me that it's spare because somebody died here and no one wants to move in!

272
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:57,510
No, wait.

273
00:13:57,511 --> 00:13:59,080
Even if he told me,

274
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:02,120
I had nowhere else to go.

275
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:06,569
 I did it because I took pity on you.

276
00:14:06,570 --> 00:14:08,329
 I took pity on you.

277
00:14:08,330 --> 00:14:10,569
 I helped you like I help the needy.

278
00:14:10,570 --> 00:14:11,480
 Got it?

279
00:14:11,481 --> 00:14:13,279
 Help the needy?

280
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:14,709
What a laugh!

281
00:14:14,710 --> 00:14:17,239
He acted like he was being generous, but he dumped this place on me

282
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:19,549
so he can at least get some rent.

283
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:21,980
Isn't that what it was?

284
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,739
No, wait.

285
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,309
At least he didn't ask for a security deposit.

286
00:14:28,310 --> 00:14:32,230
Let's pretend I didn't hear it.

287
00:14:51,630 --> 00:14:54,760
It's the Forth Industrial Revolution era.

288
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:07,010
It's the Forth Industrial Revolution era.

289
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:10,960
It's the Forth Industrial Revolution era...

290
00:15:44,980 --> 00:15:50,600
It's the Forth Industrial Revolution era...

291
00:16:21,290 --> 00:16:23,449
Was it you?

292
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:25,520
Was it you?

293
00:16:42,890 --> 00:16:46,310
 Do you want to grab a late-night snack with me, Editor Na?

294
00:16:49,190 --> 00:16:51,210
Am I going overboard when it's so late?

295
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:53,310
I shouldn't.

296
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:02,190
What? Editor Na!

297
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,599
Did someone die there?

298
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:08,080
Yes.

299
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:11,819
I couldn't stay because it feels creepy.

300
00:17:11,819 --> 00:17:14,119
So I came out to kill time.

301
00:17:14,119 --> 00:17:15,929
Did you confirm it with Hyung?

302
00:17:15,929 --> 00:17:20,539
Some even saw a body being gurneyed out...

303
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,189
You knew?

304
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:24,389
That CEO Yoo was my landlord?

305
00:17:24,390 --> 00:17:25,830
What?

306
00:17:25,830 --> 00:17:29,179
Yes. By coincidence.

307
00:17:29,180 --> 00:17:32,089
By the way, are you really going to stay here all night?

308
00:17:32,090 --> 00:17:34,129
I'll be fine.

309
00:17:34,130 --> 00:17:37,790
I've often spent the night outside doing photo shoots.

310
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:42,039
Then how about going to my second house instead?

311
00:17:42,039 --> 00:17:44,140
Your second house?

312
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:57,360
What do you think about my second house?

313
00:17:57,970 --> 00:18:00,040
It's totally amazing.

314
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:04,420
You've got a huge yard and an awesome river view.

315
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:07,239
Right?

316
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:10,209
It's the perfect spot to kill time.

317
00:18:10,210 --> 00:18:12,140
You're right.

318
00:18:18,630 --> 00:18:20,720
Looks delicious.

319
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:28,209
Do you want to order something?

320
00:18:28,209 --> 00:18:31,900
Ordering take-out here is a must.

321
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:34,970
Not again.

322
00:18:34,970 --> 00:18:37,360
Say poor backward.

323
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:41,059
But since you feel down today...

324
00:18:41,060 --> 00:18:43,369
It might sound like nagging,

325
00:18:43,370 --> 00:18:47,809
but you have to control impulse buying too.

326
00:18:47,809 --> 00:18:51,339
Okay then. How about pretending?

327
00:18:51,339 --> 00:18:54,319
- What? 
 - Here's the pizza you ordered.

328
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:56,600
Here's fried chicken.

329
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:59,320
Grilled pork belly and tteokbokki.

330
00:18:59,329 --> 00:19:04,350
This luxury set menu is only ₩5,900 ($5.90).

331
00:19:04,350 --> 00:19:07,459
Wow, Photographer Shin. You're so witty.

332
00:19:07,460 --> 00:19:10,400
You can acknowledge that I'm controlling impulse buying now, right?

333
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,540
Totally.

334
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:23,079
It's a relief.

335
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:25,199
What is?

336
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:28,670
To have a partner like you.

337
00:19:28,670 --> 00:19:32,280
If I were alone, I'd have been lonely.

338
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:35,080
You're such a great source of help.

339
00:19:39,390 --> 00:19:41,160
I'm lying.

340
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:42,970
Pardon?

341
00:19:42,970 --> 00:19:45,570
No, no I was telling the truth.

342
00:19:45,570 --> 00:19:48,180
- I was shocked. 
 - I'll buy next time.

343
00:19:48,180 --> 00:19:49,609
Okay.

344
00:19:49,609 --> 00:19:52,010
Next time, we'll...

345
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,729
Did you hear that this place is going to be redeveloped?

346
00:20:09,729 --> 00:20:12,319
If not, it doesn't look like you'd do a survey here.

347
00:20:12,319 --> 00:20:14,269
I'm not here for a survey.

348
00:20:14,269 --> 00:20:15,181
Sir?

349
00:20:15,181 --> 00:20:16,869
There's someone I have to meet.

350
00:20:16,870 --> 00:20:19,870
Did you find that woman?

351
00:20:19,870 --> 00:20:22,370
Wait here.

352
00:20:28,950 --> 00:20:30,180

353
00:20:30,180 --> 00:20:32,130

354
00:20:32,130 --> 00:20:36,320

355
00:20:58,270 --> 00:21:01,320
What? Half-deposit?

356
00:21:02,860 --> 00:21:05,609
How much?

357
00:21:05,609 --> 00:21:08,629
I see. I'll think about it.

358
00:21:08,630 --> 00:21:10,640
Okay.

359
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:14,209
What's that about a half-deposit?

360
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:15,389
It was my landlord.

361
00:21:15,390 --> 00:21:18,179
He wants a half-deposit and monthly rent now.

362
00:21:18,179 --> 00:21:22,500
Wasn't your house a luxury villa in Itaewon that was deposit-based?

363
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,340
The monthly rent will be expensive.

364
00:21:24,340 --> 00:21:26,059
It's one million won.

365
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:29,179
One million won. Every month?

366
00:21:29,179 --> 00:21:31,270
That's insane.

367
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:33,899
How can you live like that?

368
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:35,559
Why don't you just buy a place instead?

369
00:21:35,559 --> 00:21:39,209
You could get a small apartment on the outskirts of Seoul with your deposit.

370
00:21:39,210 --> 00:21:40,869
What use is that?

371
00:21:40,869 --> 00:21:42,699
House prices will fall.

372
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:46,029
Never mind that. How about a unit in my apartment complex?

373
00:21:46,030 --> 00:21:49,819
It's waiting to be redeveloped, so the deposit is really cheap.

374
00:21:49,820 --> 00:21:51,089
Forget it.

375
00:21:51,090 --> 00:21:54,469
I'd rather die than live in a rotting apartment.

376
00:21:54,470 --> 00:21:57,859
How can a person live in a place that could collapse at any moment?

377
00:21:57,859 --> 00:21:59,620
Stop. Shut up.

378
00:21:59,620 --> 00:22:03,170
How can a person...

379
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:06,500
Fine. I'm not even a person.

380
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,269
- Happy? 
 - No.

381
00:22:08,269 --> 00:22:09,560
That's not what I meant...

382
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:11,780
That redevelopment better happen soon

383
00:22:11,780 --> 00:22:14,159
because I'm not considered a person now.

384
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:17,570
It's so sad that I can't live!

385
00:22:17,570 --> 00:22:19,710
- Chief Editor... 
 - Let go!

386
00:22:20,530 --> 00:22:24,570
I said that's not what I meant!

387
00:22:34,340 --> 00:22:37,110
Hey. What do you want to eat?

388
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:39,119
How can you think about eating right now?

389
00:22:39,119 --> 00:22:41,769
The apartment you leased to Editor Na...

390
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:46,250
Is it true a former female tenant committed suicide there?

391
00:22:47,390 --> 00:22:49,119
Did Editor Na say that?

392
00:22:49,119 --> 00:22:50,609
Where did she hear that?

393
00:22:50,609 --> 00:22:52,109
Is it true?

394
00:22:52,109 --> 00:22:55,569
Let's not talk about that place. I don't even want to think about it.

395
00:22:55,569 --> 00:22:56,829
Why?

396
00:22:56,829 --> 00:22:59,210
What happened?

397
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:05,870
That woman died because of me.

398
00:23:05,870 --> 00:23:08,529
What? Did someone die there?

399
00:23:08,530 --> 00:23:10,130
Yes.

400
00:23:10,890 --> 00:23:14,349
He passed that on to you and said he helped you out of pity?

401
00:23:14,349 --> 00:23:18,830
Pretending to be kind when he's just calculating?

402
00:23:18,830 --> 00:23:21,469
That pisses me off.

403
00:23:21,469 --> 00:23:22,579
Go confront him.

404
00:23:22,580 --> 00:23:23,679
How can I?

405
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,919
I don't have anywhere else to go.

406
00:23:25,919 --> 00:23:27,779
I'm not telling you to move out.

407
00:23:27,780 --> 00:23:30,989
Ask for a discount on the monthly rent.

408
00:23:30,989 --> 00:23:32,559
Go confront him!

409
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:35,309
Even a homeless person can get angry if covered with a poop-stained newspaper!

410
00:23:35,310 --> 00:23:36,860
And a beggar can bite if you give them dog food!

411
00:23:36,860 --> 00:23:38,999
Show him what you can do!

412
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,580
Pardon?

413
00:23:41,270 --> 00:23:43,689
It's just a figure of speech.

414
00:23:43,689 --> 00:23:46,710
Anyway, go confront him.

415
00:23:46,710 --> 00:23:49,089
Forget it.

416
00:23:49,090 --> 00:23:51,410
This is frustrating.

417
00:23:52,580 --> 00:23:54,399
By the way...

418
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,329
Aren't you scared?

419
00:23:56,329 --> 00:23:57,779
I know a good psychic.

420
00:23:57,780 --> 00:23:59,239
Want a talisman?

421
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:01,640
No, it's okay.

422
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:03,979
Everything was fine until now.

423
00:24:03,979 --> 00:24:08,120
I'll pretend I didn't hear it.

424
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:10,129
Okay...

425
00:24:10,130 --> 00:24:12,550
Housing really is the problem.

426
00:24:12,550 --> 00:24:14,310
For either one of us.

427
00:24:14,319 --> 00:24:15,690
What do you mean?

428
00:24:15,690 --> 00:24:16,969
Editor Yeo.

429
00:24:16,969 --> 00:24:19,089
Did you call the interior client?

430
00:24:19,090 --> 00:24:21,019
- The single mom. 
 - Yes.

431
00:24:21,020 --> 00:24:24,099
I called her as soon as yesterday's meeting was over.

432
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:28,079
She said it was okay, but I could tell she was disappointed.

433
00:24:28,079 --> 00:24:30,809
I felt really bad.

434
00:24:30,810 --> 00:24:34,840
Yes... It was a harsh thing to do.

435
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:40,940
Did you call for me?

436
00:24:40,940 --> 00:24:43,069
The vacation home interview is set for tomorrow.

437
00:24:43,070 --> 00:24:44,570
Yes, sir.

438
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:49,180
But sir...

439
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:52,869
About the original client...

440
00:24:52,869 --> 00:24:53,811
Yes?

441
00:24:53,811 --> 00:24:57,479
She's a single mom with a 4-year-old kid.

442
00:24:57,480 --> 00:25:01,179
The single room they live in seems to be in very poor condition.

443
00:25:01,179 --> 00:25:05,689
So... Can we do two interior examples this quarter...?

444
00:25:05,689 --> 00:25:09,090
I've made my decision.

445
00:25:09,090 --> 00:25:12,809
Was that decision made because of me?

446
00:25:12,809 --> 00:25:16,419
Do you think I can't draw a line between work and private matters?

447
00:25:16,419 --> 00:25:18,150
No, sir.

448
00:25:18,150 --> 00:25:19,889
I'm sorry.

449
00:25:19,889 --> 00:25:22,409
But I am a bit scared.

450
00:25:22,409 --> 00:25:24,060
Sir?

451
00:25:25,010 --> 00:25:28,069
I'm scared to help someone now.

452
00:25:28,069 --> 00:25:30,439
I worry that people might mistake my pure intention for something else.

453
00:25:30,439 --> 00:25:33,850
I've been traumatized, you could say.

454
00:25:35,540 --> 00:25:36,899
 Go confront him!

455
00:25:36,899 --> 00:25:39,669
  Even a homeless person can get angry if covered with a poop-stained newspaper!

456
00:25:39,670 --> 00:25:41,259
 And a beggar can bite if you give them dog food!

457
00:25:41,260 --> 00:25:43,980
  Show him what you can do!

458
00:25:43,980 --> 00:25:45,150
Never mind. Get out there and—

459
00:25:45,150 --> 00:25:49,239
Your intention wasn't totally pure when you helped me!

460
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:50,200
What?

461
00:25:50,201 --> 00:25:52,000
#707.

462
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,369
I heard all about it.

463
00:25:53,369 --> 00:25:54,969
Why didn't you tell me?

464
00:25:54,969 --> 00:25:58,239
Did you worry I might not live there when you had to get rent out of it?

465
00:25:58,239 --> 00:26:00,840
Is that why you didn't tell me?

466
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:05,379
If I had told you, would you not have lived there?

467
00:26:05,379 --> 00:26:11,170
Well, I still might have, but I would've asked for a discount on rent!

468
00:26:12,660 --> 00:26:14,859
So I want to ask you.

469
00:26:14,859 --> 00:26:17,619
Give me a discount on the rent.

470
00:26:17,620 --> 00:26:20,469
No. I won't receive rent at all.

471
00:26:20,469 --> 00:26:22,160
What?

472
00:26:24,220 --> 00:26:26,429
If you go that far, it'll make me feel a little...

473
00:26:26,429 --> 00:26:28,249
Just move out.

474
00:26:28,249 --> 00:26:28,971
Sir?

475
00:26:28,971 --> 00:26:30,899
I have no intention of giving a discount on rent.

476
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:33,810
So just move out of that apartment.

477
00:26:36,540 --> 00:26:38,140
Sure.

478
00:26:38,140 --> 00:26:40,509
That's a relief!

479
00:26:40,509 --> 00:26:44,189
I had no intention of living in that creepy place.

480
00:26:44,189 --> 00:26:45,409
Fine!

481
00:26:45,409 --> 00:26:50,010
But give me some time to get a new place.

482
00:26:50,010 --> 00:26:51,980
Satisfied?

483
00:27:03,910 --> 00:27:04,790
What?

484
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,769
Pure intention?

485
00:27:06,769 --> 00:27:08,570
What a laugh!

486
00:27:08,570 --> 00:27:11,410
Do you think I won't move out if you tell me to?

487
00:27:11,410 --> 00:27:13,560
How annoying!

488
00:27:15,470 --> 00:27:16,850
Hello?

489
00:27:16,850 --> 00:27:19,580

490
00:27:19,580 --> 00:27:22,409
What did you want to talk about?

491
00:27:22,410 --> 00:27:24,119
Oh, well...

492
00:27:24,119 --> 00:27:27,079
It's about #707...

493
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:30,049
 That woman died because of me.

494
00:27:30,049 --> 00:27:31,001
 What?

495
00:27:31,001 --> 00:27:34,019
 A ridiculous rumor spread.

496
00:27:34,019 --> 00:27:37,020
 But it's far from the truth.

497
00:27:37,020 --> 00:27:40,539
  The woman in #707 was addicted to online gambling.

498
00:27:40,539 --> 00:27:44,610
 She was a nightmare of a tenant who was behind in rent for months.

499
00:27:48,790 --> 00:27:52,380
 Hyung was finally going to evict her.

500
00:27:53,620 --> 00:27:57,760

501
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:02,759
  She bore a grudge and staged a suicide

502
00:28:02,759 --> 00:28:05,490
  so the value of the apartment would drop.

503
00:28:05,490 --> 00:28:10,440
  That's why a rumor spread that someone died there.

504
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:13,629
  She disappeared, and the police are still looking for her.

505
00:28:13,629 --> 00:28:17,100
 Hyung also seems to be privately looking for her.

506
00:28:20,230 --> 00:28:23,759
He said he's not worried because it's a false rumor.

507
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:26,069
But how can he not be worried?

508
00:28:26,070 --> 00:28:28,409
- Oh, no. What should I do? 
 - Pardon?

509
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:31,830
Oh, no. This is a disaster.

510
00:28:33,310 --> 00:28:36,760

511
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:39,459
- Good job. 
 - Good job.

512
00:28:39,460 --> 00:28:41,339
When are you keeping your promise to buy drinks?

513
00:28:41,339 --> 00:28:42,441
How about today?

514
00:28:42,441 --> 00:28:44,449
I have to meet up with my cutie pie today.

515
00:28:44,449 --> 00:28:46,679
Yes, I've thought about it.

516
00:28:46,679 --> 00:28:48,589
I'll do the half-deposit and pay a monthly rent.

517
00:28:48,590 --> 00:28:49,950
Okay.

518
00:28:49,950 --> 00:28:52,259
Are you really going to pay that expensive rent?

519
00:28:52,259 --> 00:28:54,969
Yes. I can't be bothered looking for a new place.

520
00:28:54,970 --> 00:28:57,719
And I spent my own money renovating that place

521
00:28:57,719 --> 00:28:59,509
two years ago when I first moved in.

522
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:00,321
It would be such a waste to move out now.

523
00:29:00,321 --> 00:29:03,329
So why waste your own money on someone else's place?

524
00:29:03,329 --> 00:29:04,390
Why do you think?

525
00:29:04,390 --> 00:29:06,699
It's my work ethic.

526
00:29:06,699 --> 00:29:09,439
- No way. 
 - I'm an interior design article editor.

527
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:11,499
- I can't live in a dump. 
 - Sheesh.

528
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:14,439
But most of all, I like my place so much.

529
00:29:14,439 --> 00:29:17,919
There are many good restaurants, pubs, and clubs.

530
00:29:17,919 --> 00:29:20,049
Hot places are my style. You know that.

531
00:29:20,049 --> 00:29:21,580
All the more reason you should move.

532
00:29:21,580 --> 00:29:23,079
You go to restaurants, pubs, and clubs,

533
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,369
and pay an expensive rent.

534
00:29:24,370 --> 00:29:25,180
How can you manage that?

535
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:27,459
I don't know. It'll work out somehow!

536
00:29:27,459 --> 00:29:28,949
Anyway, I've made my decision.

537
00:29:28,950 --> 00:29:31,400
It's done, so don't nag at me.

538
00:29:34,340 --> 00:29:36,689
Does she work two jobs?

539
00:29:36,690 --> 00:29:38,420
She earns the same as me.

540
00:29:38,420 --> 00:29:40,530
How can she have no worries about money?

541
00:29:40,530 --> 00:29:45,930
Maybe she just didn't tell us that she's actually from a very rich family.

542
00:29:50,460 --> 00:29:51,769
I don't think so.

543
00:29:51,769 --> 00:29:52,680
Right?

544
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:55,599
She has no wealthy vibe in her bones.

545
00:29:55,599 --> 00:29:59,840
She could be dating a really rich guy.

546
00:30:06,740 --> 00:30:08,769
Let's say you're a rich guy.

547
00:30:08,770 --> 00:30:09,909
- Would you date her? 
