What a load of crap!

816
00:46:53,719 --> 00:46:54,779
I've had it!

817
00:46:54,779 --> 00:46:56,949
He maxed out! I'm going to...

818
00:46:56,949 --> 00:46:59,329
 Hold back.

819
00:46:59,329 --> 00:47:01,809
 Look at this bank book that will get you a house and hold back.

820
00:47:01,809 --> 00:47:04,669
No, I can't.

821
00:47:04,669 --> 00:47:07,029
This isn't the only magazine publisher in Korea that will hire me!

822
00:47:07,029 --> 00:47:09,219
 You're not guaranteed employment.

823
00:47:09,219 --> 00:47:11,269
 How will you live until then?

824
00:47:11,269 --> 00:47:14,019
 Look at this bank book that will help you survive and hold back.

825
00:47:14,019 --> 00:47:15,779
No.

826
00:47:15,779 --> 00:47:18,759
If I work part-time, I won't starve.

827
00:47:18,759 --> 00:47:22,450
 Then what about pu phat pong curry in Bangkok?

828
00:47:24,300 --> 00:47:26,779
I don't have to eat pu phat pong curry.

829
00:47:26,779 --> 00:47:27,939
Forget it!

830
00:47:27,939 --> 00:47:31,159
 Is your will that weak?

831
00:47:31,160 --> 00:47:33,269
 To save up, you skipped coffee.

832
00:47:33,269 --> 00:47:37,049
 You ate at convenience stores and made a ₩10,000 calendar.

833
00:47:37,049 --> 00:47:39,500
 Won't that go to waste?

834
00:47:41,690 --> 00:47:43,520
 Hold back.

835
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:47,330

836
00:47:50,820 --> 00:47:52,419
Tone it down already.

837
00:47:52,419 --> 00:47:53,929
You tone it down.

838
00:47:53,929 --> 00:47:57,380
You seem to be getting overly concerned about Editor Na these days.

839
00:47:58,020 --> 00:47:59,679
Whatever.

840
00:47:59,679 --> 00:48:02,940
Fine. I see why you're concerned.

841
00:48:03,750 --> 00:48:05,169
What?

842
00:48:05,169 --> 00:48:08,859
You must take pity on her, too.

843
00:48:08,859 --> 00:48:11,179
At her age, not having anything of her own,

844
00:48:11,179 --> 00:48:12,759
you must feel sorry.

845
00:48:12,759 --> 00:48:14,249
It's not like that.

846
00:48:14,250 --> 00:48:17,990
What do you mean it's not like that? I know what a softy you are.

847
00:48:17,990 --> 00:48:21,289
Anyway, don't keep being nice to her out of pity.

848
00:48:21,289 --> 00:48:24,530
She'll stab you in the back.

849
00:48:24,530 --> 00:48:26,629
You really hold on to a grudge.

850
00:48:26,630 --> 00:48:28,240
Stop.

851
00:48:30,120 --> 00:48:32,470
Yes, Secretary Hwang?

852
00:48:32,470 --> 00:48:34,740
Okay. I got it.

853
00:48:35,810 --> 00:48:38,839
You really won't buy the place we saw last time?

854
00:48:38,839 --> 00:48:40,869
If you don't, he's giving it to someone else.

855
00:48:40,869 --> 00:48:44,019
- I'll buy it. Draw up the contract now. 
 - Really?

856
00:48:44,019 --> 00:48:47,201
I'm going to buy it and let Editor Na live there for free.

857
00:48:47,201 --> 00:48:49,999
- What? 
 - I heard you told her to move out.

858
00:48:50,000 --> 00:48:51,569
Even if you're angry,

859
00:48:51,569 --> 00:48:54,900
how can you be so harsh to someone who has nowhere to go?

860
00:48:54,900 --> 00:48:58,139
Hey, Shin Gyeom. When will you grow up?

861
00:48:58,140 --> 00:49:01,649
Your parents aren't trying to buy you that house to run a charity!

862
00:49:01,649 --> 00:49:02,789
With that kind of weak mindset,

863
00:49:02,789 --> 00:49:05,669
